# Build Toolchain Gates

## Scope
- C++ and build files: `**/*.cpp`, `**/*.cc`, `**/*.cxx`, `**/*.h`, `**/*.hpp`, `CMakeLists.txt`, `**/*.cmake`.

## Must
- Pin minimum language and compiler versions for deterministic reference builds.
- Enforce warnings-as-errors for policy-protected targets.
- Run sanitizer matrix for eligible targets (ASan, UBSan, TSan where meaningful).
- Run pinned static-analysis config in CI and include report artifact.
- Keep CMake configuration target-scoped; avoid global compile/link flag mutation.

## Must Not
- Do not add unchecked global build flags that affect unrelated targets.
- Do not downgrade warning/sanitizer severity to bypass failing checks.

## Required Evidence
- Build matrix summary artifact with compiler/version/flags fingerprints.
- Sanitizer and static-analysis outputs attached to CI run.
